CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1963, page A10, reads: "Mrs. Gene Baker - is the wife of the Pittsburgh Pirates' coach. During the off-season the couple returns to their home in Davenport, Iowa. She loves Pittsburgh. - Harris Photos"
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Baker wearing dark silk shantung pants and shirt, holding magazine in lap, seated on light colored patterned sofa with fringe in front of two tiered side table with lamp with tilted shade
